> Grain bowl–lovers, rejoice! This week, we're serving up donburi, a Japanese rice bowl dish that can be endlessly customized with different proteins, veggies, and sauces. This version layers steamy scallion-lime rice with saucy broccoli and shredded carrots, plus perfectly fried eggs. Garnish with tangy pickled radishes and nutty sesame seeds, then finish with drizzles of sweet soy glaze and spicy sriracha. Prepare to be totally bowled over!

Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and sliced, whites and greens separated). Trim and very thinly slice @radishes{2}(very thinly sliced). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Cut @broccoli florets{8%oz} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook for ~{1%minute}. Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a small #microwave safe bowl{}, combine juice from half the lime, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, a pinch of salt and @pepper{pinch}, and a splash of water. Stir in sliced @radishes{1}(sliced). Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave for ~{1%minute}. Carefully remove plastic wrap and stir again. Set aside to pickle until ready to serve.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{3%tsp} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add broccoli, a pinch of salt and pepper, and a splash of water. Cover and steam for ~{3%minutes}. Uncover and cook, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes} more. Transfer to a #medium bowl{} and stir in @soy sauce{1%tbsp}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan. Add @shredded carrots{4%oz} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until just softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat and stir in remaining @soy sauce{1%tbsp}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a medium, preferably nonstick, #pan over medium-high heat. Crack @eggs{2} into pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry eggs to preference. Turn off heat.

Pour @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp} into a second small microwave-safe bowl; microwave until warm, ~{30%seconds}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and lime zest. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top each with broccoli, shredded carrots, and an egg. Drizzle with sweet soy glaze. Divide pickled radishes (draining first) between the centers of each bowl. Garnish with scallion greens, @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}, and @?sriracha{1%tsp} if desired. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.